    {
      "id": "b6bb98ba-e2e1-494c-b880-ba392dcc5be2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There is a plethora of studies focusing on the extraction of insights about student interaction with Learning Management Systems and its relationship to student success → problem is small samples and expensive variables. Thus, the authors use a sophisticated algorithm (unspecified) with what they call low cost variables to make early prediction of success in large courses. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "b6bb98ba-e2e1-494c-b880-ba392dcc5be2",
        "parent": {
